h2. *Create new collection*

called PermissionFieldsMapping, to map a permission --> many java-field-names. Example structure:

{code:java}{
\xa0 \xa0 "id": "102",
\xa0 \xa0 "accountUid": "123", // customer account
\xa0 \xa0 "permission": "view_cdf",\xa0
\xa0 \xa0 "fields": ["cdf.abc"],
\xa0 \xa0 "isDefaultMapping": false,
\xa0 \xa0 "isDeleted": false // posible to soft delete
\xa0 \xa0 "orginalMappingId": "100" // override the default
},\xa0
{
\xa0 \xa0 "id": "101",
\xa0 \xa0 "accountUid": "123", // customer account
\xa0 \xa0 "permission": "view_custom",\xa0
\xa0 \xa0 "fields": ["username", "domain"],
\xa0 \xa0 "isDefaultMapping": false,
\xa0 \xa0 "isDeleted": false\xa0
},\xa0
{
\xa0 \xa0 "id": "100",
\xa0 \xa0 "accountUid": "000", // Abs default
\xa0 \xa0 "permission": "view_cdf", // permission from URP
\xa0 \xa0 "fields": ["cdf", "rdf"], // DeviceReport java field
\xa0 \xa0 "isDefaultMapping": true, // the default mapping, can not be deleted
\xa0 \xa0 "isDeleted": false
}{code}

h2. *API to CRUD the mapping*

There is a set of default mappings provided by Absolute. Customer can add/modify/delete. Mechanism is similar to [https://myabsolute.atlassian.net/wiki/display/PEG/EUM+-+Predefined+message+templates+for+EUM|https://myabsolute.atlassian.net/wiki/display/PEG/EUM+-+Predefined+message+templates+for+EUM]

