h2. *Catch and modify QueryObject before executing query*

Find the corresponding permission of user of the incoming request

Depend on view_default is checked or not, to reject or include/exclude the field in select.

{code:java}Map<String, List<String>> permissionFields = new HashMap<>(); // get from database and create a map
permissionFields.put("view_cdf", Arrays.asList("cdf.abc"));
permissionFields.put("view_device_freeze", Arrays.asList("dfStatus"));
permissionFields.put("view_custom", Arrays.asList("username", "domain"));
List<String> permissions = new ArrayList<>(Arrays.asList("view_default", "view_cdf", "view_custom")); // get from URM/URP
if (permissions.contains("view_default")) { // we need to exclude fields
    permissions.remove("view_default");
    permissions.forEach(permissionFields::remove);
    Set<String> fieldsToExclude = permissionFields.values().stream().flatMap(Collection::stream).collect(Collectors.toSet());
    // check if QueryObject has any excluded field in filter, select or sort --> reject the request
    // if QueryObject.select is empty, exclude these fields
    System.out.println(fieldsToExclude);
}
else { // mean the view_default is not checked, so just show the fields that has permission
    Set<String> includeFields = permissionFields.entrySet().stream().filter(entry -> permissions.contains(entry.getKey()))
            .map(Map.Entry::getValue)
            .flatMap(Collection::stream).collect(Collectors.toSet());
    // check if QueryObject has any key that do not in the list --> reject the request
    // if QueryObject.select is empty, include the field
    System.out.println(includeFields);
}{code}

h2. Modify common odata2query

to able to exclude the fields

[https://bitbucket.absolute.com/projects/DDSCJ/repos/odata2query/browse/odata2query-adapter/src/main/java/com/absolute/odata2query/adapter/impl/SpringDataAdapter.java#186|https://bitbucket.absolute.com/projects/DDSCJ/repos/odata2query/browse/odata2query-adapter/src/main/java/com/absolute/odata2query/adapter/impl/SpringDataAdapter.java#186]

CHEAT: do not need to create a new flag in QueryObject

{code:java}@Override 
public void applySelectFields(QueryObject queryObject, Query query) {
    List<SelectField> selects = queryObject.getSelect();
    if (selects == null || selects.isEmpty()) {
        return;
    }

    if (selects.get(0).getField().equals("exclude")) {
        selects.remove(0);
        for (SelectField selectField : selects) {
            query.fields().exclude(selectField.getField());
        }
        return;
    }
    for (SelectField selectField : selects) {
        query.fields().include(selectField.getField());
    }
}{code}

